<section class="member-post--summary"><p>On behalf of the Spring Data team I’d like to announce the general availability of our <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daniel_Henry_Holmes_Ingalls_Jr.">Ingalls</a> release train. After nine months of development, this release not only contains a huge set of new features, improvements and bug fixes, it also marks the conclusion of a branch of Spring Data that has helped developers dealing with persistence for more than 5 years — even 8, if you count in some module’s predecessors.</p>
<p>The release ships more than 630 tickets fixed in total. Here’s a very truncated list of the most important features shipping with the release:</p>
